However, his sizable salary presents difficulties in finding a trade partner before the summer.
title: Chicago Blackhawks 'considering trading goalie Petr Mrazek for free'

description: Senior IPS officer DGP Ramachandra Rao has distanced himself from his stepdaughter, Kannada actress Ranya Rao, following her arrest in a gold smuggling case. Ranya was caught at Bengaluru Airport with 14.8 kg of gold worth Rs 12.56 crore. Authorities suspect her involvement in a larger smuggling network. DGP Rao asserted his lack of knowledge of her actions.
title: Gold smuggling case: Ranya Rao's stepfather DGP himself from case

description: More than 70 people were killed and dozens wounded in clashes between Syrian security forces and Assad loyalists in Latakia. The violence began when pro-Assad fighters attacked security checkpoints, prompting helicopter strikes. The fighting is the most intense since Assad's ouster in December, and security forces are now working to restore order in Jableh.
title: Over 70 killed, dozens hurt in clashes with Assad loyalists in Syria

description: US President Donald Trump signed an executive order to establish a government-held Bitcoin reserve, leading to a significant price drop for Bitcoin. The reserve will include around 200,000 bitcoins seized from criminal and civil proceedings and will not be sold, in order to act as a store of value.
title: 'Promises kept': Trump signs executive order to establish US Bitcoin reserve

description: Stock market recommendations: Adani Ports and Axis Bank are top stock picks, as per Bajaj Broking Research. Nifty's expected to extend a pullback towards 22,800, while Bank Nifty consolidates in the range of 47,800-50,500.
title: Top stocks to buy today: Stock recommendations for March 7

description: President Donald Trump signed an executive order directing government lawyers to request bonds from plaintiffs suing his policies. This potentially imposes financial barriers for challengers, holding them liable for government costs if their case is lost. This response targets the numerous lawsuits against Trump's administrative changes, though judges are not obligated to grant these bond requests.
title: Trump mandates upfront bond payments in lawsuits challenging his policies

description: Ankita Lokhande revisits her childhood home in Indore, accompanied by her husband Vicky Jain and mother Vandana Pandis Lokhande. The couple tours the city's notable spots, indulging in nostalgic memories, and emotionally reconnects with Ankita's past at her grandmother's house.
title: Vicky Jain reacts in refusal to Ankita suggesting couple counselling for them

description: Donald Trump assured stranded astronauts Sunita Williams and Butch Wilmore that efforts are underway for their return, blaming Joe Biden for their situation. Originally planned as an 8-day mission, technical faults in the Boeing Starliner have kept them in space since June 2024. They may return to Earth in March 2025 aboard a SpaceX vehicle.
title: What Donald Trump said on astronaut Sunita Williams’ hair

description: Tamil Nadu CM MK Stalin criticises the Centre's three-language formula under NEP 2020, terming it 'Hindi colonialism'. He asserts Tamil Nadu will not tolerate this and mocks the BJP's signature campaign. Stalin emphasizes that Hindi has been overly imposed, while the Tamil Nadu BJP chief counters his claims and backs the policy.
title: 'Won't tolerate Hindi colonialism': Stalin's fresh attack on Centre over language row
Watch: SpaceX Starship explodes mid-air, fiery debris streaks across Bahamas sky

description: Israeli authorities have successfully rescued ten Indian construction workers from the West Bank after they were held for over a month, with their passports confiscated. The operation, involving multiple Israeli agencies, uncovered a scheme where Palestinians used the Indians' passports to attempt illegal entry into Israel.
title: Israel rescues 10 Indian workers from West Bank after month-long captivity

description: SpaceX launched another Starship rocket from Texas, but contact was lost minutes into the flight, causing it to spiral out of control. The mission aimed to deploy four mock satellites but failed as engines shut down prematurely. SpaceX recovered the first-stage booster, though the spacecraft ultimately lost stability and did not complete its mission.
title: SpaceX loses contact with Starship during latest test flight

description: New Zealand are set to strategize smarter for the Champions Trophy final against India, mindful of the Indian team's spin-heavy approach. Veteran Ambati Rayudu highlights Mitchell Santner's spin, Rachin Ravindra's explosive top-order batting and Devon Conway's potential threat as key threats to watch out for India in the title clash on Sunday.
title: Three things India must be wary of in CT final vs New Zealand

description: Chhaava, starring Vicky Kaushal, has been performing exceptionally well since its release on February 14. Despite a significant drop in its third week, the film has grossed Rs 483.58 crore in India and is poised to possibly cross the Rs 500 crore mark over the weekend. Directed by Laxman Utekar, it also features Akshaye Khanna and Rashmika Mandanna.
title: Vicky Kaushal starrer 'Chhaava' wraps up third week with Rs 84 crore

description: A 27-year-old man from Pimple Nilakh set 13 two-wheelers on fire in a housing society's parking lot after arguing with his family. The incident occurred around 3:30 am on Wednesday. A 62-year-old resident filed a complaint, and police have booked the suspect but have not yet arrested him.
title: Pune man quarrels at home, goes out and burns 13 vehicles

description: An investigation has revealed a human trafficking network in Visakhapatnam linked to cyber scam centres in Myanmar. Victims were lured with false job promises and sold into cyber slavery for $3,500 each. They were forced to manage fake profiles and withstand severe punishments. Adam, the agent behind this, threatened victims when they attempted to expose the scam.
title: From Vizag to Myanmar: Cyber slavery footprint gets bigger

description: Noida International Airport's launch is postponed beyond April due to delays in terminal construction, specifically for international passengers. DGCA and BCAS clearances, essential for commercial operations, are also pending. Domestic services may start earlier, with the timeline to be decided in a meeting led by CM Yogi Adityanath.
title: Noida airport to miss April date, 2nd delay in timeline

description: A tribal school headmaster in Gadchiroli's Kukkametta village was arrested for indecent exposure to minor schoolgirls. Ravindra Gawhare, 45, threatened the girls with murder and expulsion if they disclosed the incidents. The case came to light when two girls refused to attend school. Police have taken him into custody and are investigating under IPC and Pocso Act provisions.
title: Teacher held for flashing at minor girls, threatening to murder them in Gadchiroli

description: There were reports taking the internet by storm about the breakup of Tamannaah Bhatia and her beau, Vijay Varma. After the reports went viral on the internet, netizens were curious to know the reason, and many were heartbroken upon hearing the sad news. Now, Tamannaah has finally shared her perspective on the concept of love and the difference between love and relationships.
title: Tamannaah Bhatia talks about difference between love and relationships

description: The Directorate of Revenue Intelligence detained Sandalwood actor Ranya Rao at the Kempegowda International Airport for gold smuggling, seizing nearly 15kg of gold. Additional searches uncovered gold ornaments and cash at her residence. Ranya's connection to a smuggling syndicate is under investigation. Her father, DGP Rao, claims ignorance of her activities. Bail decision pending.
title: Karnataka DGP's daughter Ranya Rao threat to national security: DRI

description: Elon Musk responded to President Donald Trump's praise during a joint Congress address, emphasizing his commitment to America. Musk stressed that he seeks no personal gain, only striving for the nation's progress. The President lauded Musk's leadership of the Department of Government Efficiency (DOGE).
title: Elon Musk's emphatic 'one-word' reply to 'will fight for & die in America' post

description: A 30-year-old software engineer, Mayank Rajani, allegedly jumped to his death from the 12th floor of his Bengaluru apartment over health issues and startup losses. Rajani had previously undergone spinal surgery and experienced mental distress. The incident is under investigation as an unnatural death.
title: 'Loss in startup': Techie jumps to death from 12th floor Bengaluru flat
